    {
      "content": "This topic describes the security and privacy considerations related to Cloud App Discovery.",
      "pos": [
        101,
        193
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Cloud App Discovery Security and Privacy Considerations",
      "pos": [
        507,
        562
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Microsoft is committed to protecting your privacy and securing your data, while delivering software and services that help you manage the security of your organization.",
      "pos": [
        564,
        732
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "We recognize that when you entrust your data to others, that trust requires rigorous security engineering investments and expertise to back it.",
      "pos": [
        738,
        881
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Microsoft adheres to strict compliance and security guidelines from secure software development lifecycle practices to operating a service.",
      "pos": [
        882,
        1021
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Securing and protecting data is a top priority at Microsoft.",
      "pos": [
        1027,
        1087
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This topic explains how data is collected, processed, and secured within Azure Active Directory Cloud App Discovery",
      "pos": [
        1089,
        1204
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Overview",
      "pos": [
        1211,
        1219
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Cloud App Discovery is a feature of Azure AD and is hosted in Microsoft Azure.",
      "pos": [
        1221,
        1299
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The Cloud App Discovery endpoint agent is used to collect application discovery data from IT managed machines.",
      "pos": [
        1305,
        1415
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The collected data is sent securely over an encrypted channel to the Azure AD Cloud App Discovery service.",
      "pos": [
        1421,
        1527
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The Cloud App Discovery data for an organization is then visible in the Azure portal.",
      "pos": [
        1533,
        1618
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "How Cloud App Discovery Works",
      "pos": [
        1636,
        1665
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following sections follow the flow of information and describe how it is secured as it moves from your organization to the Cloud App Discovery service and ultimately to the Cloud App Discovery portal.",
      "pos": [
        1774,
        1978
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Collecting data from your organization",
      "pos": [
        1985,
        2023
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In order to use Azure Active Directory’s Cloud App discovery feature to get insights into the applications used by employees in your organization, you need to first deploy the Azure AD Cloud App Discovery endpoint agent to machines in your organization.",
      "pos": [
        2025,
        2278
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Administrators of the Azure Active Directory tenant (or their delegate) can download the agent installation package from the Azure portal.",
      "pos": [
        2280,
        2418
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The agent can either be manually installed or installed across multiple machines in the organization using SCCM or Group Policy.",
      "pos": [
        2419,
        2547
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For further instructions on deployment options, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Cloud App Discovery Group Policy Deployment Guide<ept id=\"p1\">](http://social.technet.microsoft.com/wiki/contents/articles/30965.cloud-app-discovery-group-policy-deployment-guide.aspx)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2549,
        2774
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Data collected by the agent",
      "pos": [
        2785,
        2812
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The information outlined in the list below is collected by the agent when a connection is made to a Web application.",
      "pos": [
        2814,
        2930
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The information is only collected for those applications that the administrator has configured for discovery.",
      "pos": [
        2931,
        3040
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can edit the list of cloud apps that the agent monitors through the Cloud App Discovery blade in the Microsoft <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure portal<ept id=\"p1\">](https://portal.azure.com)</ept>, under <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Settings<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>-&gt;<bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Data Collection<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>-&gt;<bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>App Collection list<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        3046,
        3268
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more details, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Getting Started With Cloud App Discovery<ept id=\"p1\">](http://social.technet.microsoft.com/wiki/contents/articles/30962.getting-started-with-cloud-app-discovery.aspx)</ept>",
      "pos": [
        3269,
        3445
      ]
    },
    {
